<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="width: 100% !important" ><tbody><tr><td align="center"><table style=" border: 1px solid #d1d1d1; border-radius: 5px; margin: 40px 0; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; color: #2d3748; " width="600" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" ><tbody><tr><td align="center" style="padding: 0;"><div style=" text-align: left; width: 100%; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.4; " ><div style="margin: 30px 36px"><a href="${serverUrl}"><img src="${serverUrl+'/files-api/api/get/raw/logo/IBP.png'}" alt="${siteName}" style="width: 180px" /></a></div><a href="${serverUrl+'/observation/list'}"><img src="${serverUrl+'/biodiv/assets/all/picturebanner.png'}" alt="" style="width: 100%" /></a><div style="padding: 30px 40px"><p>Hi ${username},</p><p> You are now part of an exciting initiative designed to facilitate participation and enable open access for all citizens in contributing information on biodiversity for the benefit of science and society. All data on the portal is free and served under Creative Commons license. </p><p>How to get Started:</p><div style="display: flex; margin-bottom: 1.6rem"><img src="${serverUrl+'/biodiv/newsletters/welcome/user.png'}" style="width: 100px; height: 100px; margin-right: 24px" alt="User" /><div><a href="${serverUrl+userProfileUrl}">Complete your user profile</a> Upload a photo, write a few words on your interests to help other users know more about you. View other profiles, and compare your <a href="${serverUrl+'/user/leaderboard/'}">leaderboard ranking</a></div></div><div style="display: flex; margin-bottom: 1.6rem"><img src="${serverUrl+'/biodiv/newsletters/welcome/observations.png'}" style="width: 100px; height: 100px; margin-right: 24px" alt="Observations" /><div><a href="${serverUrl+'/observation/list'}"> Participate in citizen science </a> Upload, identify, browse or download observations of flora and fauna that you observe to help curate occurrence data on species around you. </div></div><div style="display: flex; margin-bottom: 1.6rem"><img src="${serverUrl+'/biodiv/newsletters/welcome/species.png'}" style="width: 100px; height: 100px; margin-right: 24px" alt="Species" /><div><a href="${serverUrl+'/species/list'}"> Learn about species </a> Browse through curated species page information, to know more about them. If you are a species expert, you may <a href="${serverUrl+'/species/contribute'}">request</a> to be a species page contributor. </div></div><div style="display: flex; margin-bottom: 1.6rem"><img src="${serverUrl+'/biodiv/newsletters/welcome/naksha.png'}" style="width: 100px; height: 100px; margin-right: 24px" alt="Naksha" /><div><a href="${serverUrl+'/maps'}"> Visualize or download maps </a> Interact with spatial data on biodiversity through our map layers. The layers can be overlaid and queried or downloaded to be used offline. </div></div><div style="display: flex; margin-bottom: 1.6rem"><img src="${serverUrl+'/biodiv/newsletters/welcome/documents.png'}" style="width: 100px; height: 100px; margin-right: 24px" alt="Observations" /><div><a href="${serverUrl+'/document/list'}"> Browse or upload documents </a> Access scholarly publications and grey literature on an array of topics relevant to biodiversity, contributed by users. </div></div><div style="display: flex; margin-bottom: 1.6rem"><img src="${serverUrl+'/biodiv/newsletters/welcome/community.png'}" style="width: 100px; height: 100px; margin-right: 24px" alt="Observations" /><div><a href="${serverUrl+'/usergroup/list'}"> Join user communities </a> Groups are microsites on various, taxonomic, spatial or organizational themes that you may join to interact with and help build information on. </div></div><p> We're excited to have you as a member. Thank you for joining and we hope you enjoy using the portal. </p><p> Regards,<br /> The ${siteName} Team </p><hr style=" border: none; border-top: 1px solid #eaeaea; margin: 32px 0; width: 100%; " /><p style="color: #666; font-size: 14px; line-height: 24px"> Please add <i>${mailDefaultFrom}</i> to your address book to ensure you continue to receive emails from us in your inbox. </p></div></div></td></tr></tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table>
